    <title>「git-push-url」Push multiple repositories (en)</title>
    <link href="http://example.com/2022/08/01/git-push-url(en)/"/>
    <id>http://example.com/2022/08/01/git-push-url(en)/</id>
    <published>2022-08-01T10:20:05.000Z</published>
    <updated>2022-10-08T17:43:46.361Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>when we want to push multiple repo:</p><ul><li><p>multiple remote (the commonly used： git remote add origin <git_repo_url>)</p></li><li><p>multiple urls below same remote (similarly: git remote set-url origin <git_repo_url>)</p></li></ul><p>In “set-url” can’t add urls, it just replace url.</p><p>The purpose of this tool is to simply add urls, and yes, it is that simple.</p><h2 id="Use-For"><a href="#Use-For" class="headerlink" title="Use For"></a>Use For</h2><p>Push multiple repositories</p><h2 id="Usage"><a href="#Usage" class="headerlink" title="Usage"></a>Usage</h2><pre class="line-numbers language-bash" data-language="bash"><code class="language-bash"><span class="token function">npm</span> i git-push-url -ggit-push-url <span class="token function">add</span> https://github.com/user/repo.git<span class="token comment">#or</span>git-push-url remove https://github.com/user/repo.git<span aria-hidden="true" class="line-numbers-rows"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></code></pre><h2 id="Principle"><a href="#Principle" class="headerlink" title="Principle"></a>Principle</h2><blockquote><p>Changed the remote content in the <strong>“.&#x2F;.git&#x2F;config”</strong> file in the current directory, adding or removing the URL.</p></blockquote><p>Welcome to contribute. </p><p>github: <a href="https://github.com/weykon/git-push-url">https://github.com/weykon/git-push-url</a></p>]]></content>
    
    
      
      
    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;when we want to push multiple repo:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;multiple remote (the commonly used： git remote add origin &lt;git_repo_url&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;</summary>
      
    
    
    
    
